# Vanilla Theme Development

## When to use
- Building or modifying the Spotify community theme in `vanillaforums/spotify`
- Creating new theme assets (header, footer, styles, variables)
- Understanding how Vanilla's theme system works
- Debugging theme rendering issues

## Theme Architecture

Vanilla has two theme generations. **Always use the modern "asset-based" approach** (DataDrivenTheme) for new work.

### Modern Asset-Based Theme (recommended)

Themes live in `themes/<theme-name>/` with this structure:

```
themes/<name>/
  addon.json              # Theme manifest (key, name, features, assets)
  package.json            # npm config for build tooling
  <Name>ThemeHooks.php    # PHP hooks class (extends Gdn_Plugin)
  README.md
  assets/
    header.twig           # Custom HTML above Vanilla's React header
    footer.twig           # Custom footer HTML
    styles.css            # Scoped CSS for header/footer only
    variables.neon        # Design tokens (colours, fonts, spacing)
  design/
    custom.css            # Main CSS override file (applies globally)
  js/
    custom.js             # Client-side JavaScript
  src/
    scss/custom.scss      # SCSS source (compiled to design/custom.css)
    scripts/
      entries/forum.tsx   # Webpack/Vite entry point
  views/
    layout.default.twig   # Master page template
    components/           # Twig partials
    categories/           # Category view overrides (PHP)
    discussions/          # Discussion list view overrides (PHP)
    discussion/           # Single discussion view overrides (PHP)
```

### addon.json

```json
{
  "key": "theme-name",
  "name": "Theme Display Name",
  "type": "theme",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "hidden": false,
  "mobileFriendly": true,
  "Features": {
    "DataDrivenTheme": true,
    "SharedMasterView": true
  },
  "assets": {
    "variables": "assets/variables.neon",
    "header": "assets/header.twig",
    "footer": "assets/footer.twig",
    "styles": "assets/styles.css"
  }
}
```

Key fields:
- `"DataDrivenTheme": true` — opts into React header/nav system
- `"SharedMasterView": true` — uses the platform's shared master view
- `"hidden": true` — hides from theme picker (used during development)
- `assets` — declares which files are loaded as theme assets

### variables.neon

The token system that controls the entire theme appearance. Override only what you need; everything else falls back to defaults.

```neon
# Primary brand colours
global:
    mainColors:
        primary: "#1DB954"       # Spotify green
        bg: "#121212"            # Dark background
        fg: "#FFFFFF"            # Light text
    fonts:
        forceGoogleFont: "Circular, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"
    body:
        backgroundImage:
            color: "#121212"

# Title bar / navigation
titleBar:
    colors:
        bg: "#000000"
        fg: "#FFFFFF"

# Banner area
banner:
    colors:
        primary: "#1DB954"
        bg: "#191414"

# Content tiles
tiles:
    options:
        columns: 2
```

Common token paths: `global.mainColors`, `global.fonts`, `titleBar`, `banner`, `shadow`, `tiles`, `navigation`, `links`, `border`.

### PHP Hooks (ThemeHooks.php)

```php
class MyThemeHooks extends Gdn_Plugin {
    public function setup() {
        // Runs on theme activation
        saveToConfig('Garden.HomepageTitle', 'Spotify Community');
    }

    public function base_render_before($sender) {
        // Fires on every page render — add assets, set metadata
        $sender->addCssFile('custom.css', 'themes/my-theme/design');
        $sender->addJsFile('custom.js', 'themes/my-theme/js');
    }

    public function discussionController_beforeDiscussionRender_handler($sender) {
        // Fires before a single discussion renders
        $sender->Head->addTag('meta', ['name' => 'threadid', 'content' => $sender->data('Discussion.DiscussionID')]);
    }
}
```

Common hook points:
- `base_render_before` — every page (add CSS/JS, set metadata)
- `discussionController_beforeDiscussionRender_handler` — single discussion page
- `categoryController_beforeCategoriesRender_handler` — category listing
- `categoriesController_beforeCategoriesRender_handler` — categories index

### Twig Templates

`layout.default.twig` is the master template. Key Twig variables:

```twig
{{ vanillaUrl }}              {# Base URL of the Vanilla site #}
{{ cssUrl }}                  {# URL to the theme's CSS #}
{{ heroImageUrl }}            {# Banner image URL #}
{{ title }}                   {# Page title #}
{{ locale }}                  {# Current locale code #}
{{ isHomepage }}              {# Boolean: is this the homepage? #}
{% block content %}           {# Main content block #}
  {{ Content.render()|raw }}
{% endblock %}
```

### Discussion/Comment PHP Views

Legacy PHP view files override Vanilla's default rendering:
- `writeComment($comment, $sender)` — renders a single comment/post
- `writeDiscussionRow($discussion, $sender, $session)` — renders a discussion list row
- `writeTableHead()` / `writeTableRow()` — table-based category listings

These use `Gdn_Theme` helpers and `Gdn_Format::text()` / `Gdn_Format::to()` for content formatting.

## Deploy Pipeline

### deploy.json

```json
{
  "production": {
    "branch": "master",
    "id": "6038735"
  },
  "staging": {
    "branch": "stage",
    "id": "6038846"
  },
  "development": {
    "branch": "develop",
    "id": "6038847"
  }
}
```

Deploy via Vanilla's "Theme Pull" button in the forum dashboard (Settings > Theme). Each branch maps to a site ID. No GitHub Actions or CI — deployment is manual pull from dashboard.

### Branch strategy
- `master` — production-ready code
- `stage` — staging/QA
- `develop` — active development
- Feature branches: `feature/*` or `fix/*`, PR into `develop`

